snippet.textDisplay:
Of COURSE you can't relax. Your in a hot tub with 7 other people. All of you not even certain who you are. Yet, your in a hot tub with them. HOW could you Relax?
Socrates said, "Know thy self". He didn't say this philosophically, he meant, " know your Self"..
What do you think, like, Need, what are your do not Cross boundaries? What are your biggest fears? What brings you Peace?
Have you ever experienced a quiet peaceful and happy mind? These are all genuinely possible moments. Relaxing is easy when we can be quiet within, observing a unified world.
I found peace being lead through the 12 steps in a sobriety 12 step group.
It's a way to confront all our fears and horrible actions, make a healthy balanced amends, and release all the real and false guilt.
Peace of mind, of Spirit, is incredible. I just want to help. I'm sure there are other options I just don't know them.
